         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">No. 7f ¶ Kew, Sept 24/68 ¶ My dear Sir Henry ¶  ¶ […] ¶  ¶ I have been 10 days in Scotland […] and passed a few days with my friend Sir F. Rogers at his brother-in-law's in Fife....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M68.09.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker to Henry Barkly</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, archives, Letters from Joseph Hooker vol., Ada-Bar, ff. 172-4.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Hooker to H. Barkly, 9 October 1865 (in this edition as M65-10-09), n. 1.</p>
               </note>No. 7f</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Kew, Sept 24/68</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir Henry</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Text not relevant to M has been replaced by an ellipsis here and below. The text given here is on f. 173.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been 10 days in Scotland […] and passed a few days with my friend Sir F. Rogers at his brother-in-law's in Fife.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I urged Mueller's claims for Knighthood<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also J. Hooker to H. Barkly, 9 October 1865 (in this edition as M65-10-09).</p>
               </note> and Sir F. seemed very favorably disposed, but told me how foolish M. had been in craving the liberty to wear his foreign orders. I fear the poor fellow spoils his own sport: I hear from him by every mail almost; and his zeal scarcely flags — he is as determined as ever about Leichardt's remains being recoverable […]</p>
